Comment: A move that leads, if followed up properly, to a solid [albeit somewhat cramped] position for Black.
This move compels Black to concede a minor exchange...
...after this reply, in order to avoid losing material.
White now has an advantage in development, and incidentally threatens the weak spot at Black's KB2.
Shielding the weakness from the White Q.
The fatal error. Further development was called for. 7... Q-Q2 adds valuable protection to the KBP, and even 7... B-K2 would create a flight square.
Black cannot interpose or capture, so he must move his K.
8... K-K2 also falls victim to White's next move.
